It depend of your opponent, you can choose to bid between 3-5 (you can remove 2 with ringbound).  If you suspect Archery or another Swarm let him start if not it&#39;s your choice. golden hall is very good again Trust  me deck (for the bow and the axe). The objectif of the fellow is to set your shadow and = draw and you can choke him. result he keep his shadows cards in hand. Normaly I start and I move 1-2, 2-3, 3-5, 5-6, 6-8, 8-9. But if you draw the Dark place you can move first to 7 .<br />
<br />
Shadow:<br />
Classic Moria swarm, but with the goblin sneak= because I hate when I don&#39;t have enough card in my deck at the end with him I am sure to draw  cheap minions at the end! the 39th card can be anything I change it regulary I don&#39;t know which is the best.<br />
<br />
Faramir + Last alliance = death to anything with 9 of power or less<br />
<br />
P.S. I try this version of the deck but I played a lot with variation, the shadow kill most of the deck that don&#39;t have condition removal, but  he have difficulty vs Trust me (bow if galandhrim , gimli&#39;s Axe, albert, GST....) The Fellowship is slow at the start but he can double at the hand when you are set.  If you expect a lot of Uruk and saruman play 1x Betrayal of isengard vs Bill or another Foul creation.<br />
